{"id":15390,"date":"2013-07-24T22:12:50","date_gmt":"2013-07-24T18:12:50","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=15390"},"modified":"2019-05-19T12:20:34","modified_gmt":"2019-05-19T08:20:34","slug":"saying-amin-aloud-surah-fatihah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/24\/saying-amin-aloud-surah-fatihah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Salat: Saying ameen aloud after Surat al-Fatihah"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Wa&#8217;il ibn Hujr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would recite the verse, \u201c<b>Not those who have earned anger, nor who go astray<\/b>,\u201d (1:7) and he would say with a raised voice, \u201c<b>Ameen<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cMore than one of the people of knowledge among the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, their successors, and those after them narrated that a man should raise his voice to say <i>ameen<\/i> and he should not make it silent. Such was said by Al-Shafi&#8217;i, Ahmad, and Ishaq.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 248<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan<\/i> (fair) according to Al-Nawawi<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0644\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062d\u064f\u062c\u0652\u0631\u064d \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e <b>\u063a\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u063a\u0652\u0636\u064f\u0648\u0628\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u0645\u0652 \u0648\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0636\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0651\u064a\u0646\u064e<\/b> \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e <b>\u0622\u0645\u0650